                    <lb n="4"/><gap reason="lost" quantity="9" unit="character" precision="low"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#_ης" type="patronymic"><seg part="F">ευς</seg></name></persName>, 
                    τ<supplied reason="lost">ῶ</supplied> <persName type="divine" ref="#Apollo"><name nymRef="#Ἀπόλλων"><supplied reason="lost">Ἀπ</supplied><lb n="5" break="no"/><supplied reason="lost">όλλωνος</supplied></name></persName> <rs type="office" key="eponymous priest"><w lemma="ἱαριτεύω"><supplied reason="lost">ἱ</supplied><unclear>α</unclear>ριτεύον<supplied reason="lost">τος</supplied></w></rs>                    
                    <lb n="6"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Θεύχρηστος"><supplied reason="lost" cert="low">Θευχρήσ</supplied>τω</name> <persName type="attested" key=""><name type="patronymic" nymRef="#Πολύτιμος">Πολυτί<unclear>μ</unclear><supplied reason="lost">ω</supplied></name></persName></persName>.                    
                    <lb n="7"/><w lemma="καρπός"><supplied reason="lost">Καρπὸς</supplied></w> <w lemma="τιμάω"><supplied reason="lost">ἐτ</supplied>ιμάθη</w>· 
                        <g type="punct">:</g> <w lemma="κριθά">κρι<supplied reason="lost">θαὶ</supplied></w>
                    <lb n="8"/><w><supplied reason="lost">ἀν</supplied></w> <gap reason="lost" quantity="3" unit="character" precision="low"/>· 
                        <w lemma="σπυρός"><supplied reason="lost">σπυ</supplied>ροὶ</w> <g type="punct">:</g> <w>ἀν</w>  
                        <num type="total" value="2">
                            <measure type="currency" unit="drachma">
                                <num value="2">
                                    <g type="cyrnum">𐅝</g>
                                </num>
                            </measure>
                        </num>·
                        <w lemma="ὄσπριον"><unclear>ὄ</unclear><supplied reason="lost">σπρια</supplied></w>
                    <lb n="9"/><w><supplied reason="lost">ἀν</supplied></w> <gap reason="lost" quantity="4" unit="character" precision="low"/>·
                    <w lemma="σταφίς"><supplied reason="lost">στ</supplied>αφὶς</w> <w>ἀν</w> <gap reason="lost" quantity="3" unit="character" precision="low"/> <w lemma="σῦκον"><supplied reason="lost">σῦκα</supplied></w>
                    <lb n="10"/><gap reason="lost" quantity="4" unit="character" precision="low"/>·
                    <w lemma="σταφυλά"><supplied reason="lost">σταφυλὰ</supplied></w> <w lemma="ψύθιος">ψυ<supplied reason="lost">θία</supplied></w> <w><supplied reason="lost">ἔνδο</supplied><lb n="11" break="no"/><supplied reason="lost">ς</supplied></w> <supplied reason="lost">τᾶς</supplied> <w lemma="προκλησία"><supplied reason="lost">προ</supplied>κ<supplied reason="lost">λησίας</supplied></w> <w><supplied reason="lost">ἀν</supplied></w> <gap reason="lost" quantity="4" unit="character" precision="low"/>:
                    <lb n="11a"/> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="line"/>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p><app loc="1"><lem resp="#marengo-paci1998 #IGCyr"><supplied reason="lost">Θεοί</supplied></lem>
                <rdg resp="#rosamilia2023"><supplied reason="lost">Θεοί· δαμιεργέντων</supplied><note>This display is as plausible as the one with 'Gods' on one head-line.</note></rdg>
                </app>
                    <app loc="3"><lem resp="#marengo-paci1998 #IGCyr"><orig>πι</orig></lem>
                    <rdg resp="#rosamilia2023"><orig><unclear>ν</unclear>ι</orig></rdg>
                    </app>
                    <app loc="6"><lem resp="#rosamilia2023"><supplied reason="lost" cert="low">Θευχρήσ</supplied>τω</lem>
                    <rdg resp="#marengo-paci1998 IGCyr"><gap reason="lost" quantity="8" unit="character" precision="low"/><seg part="F">τω</seg> Πολυτί<unclear>μ</unclear><supplied reason="lost">ω</supplied></rdg>
                    </app>
                    <app loc="9"><lem resp="#rosamilia2023"><gap reason="lost" quantity="3" unit="character" precision="low"/> <supplied reason="lost">σῦκα</supplied></lem>
                    <rdg resp="#marengo-paci1998 #IGCyr"><gap reason="lost" quantity="7" unit="character" precision="low"/></rdg></app>
                </p>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p><supplied reason="lost">Dieux. Etant démiurges Untel fils d'Untel, Untel fils d'Untel, Untel</supplied> fils de <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>ès, étant prêtre d'Apollon <supplied reason="lost" cert="low">Theukhres</supplied>tos 
            fils de Polytimos, <supplied reason="lost">la récolte</supplied> a été estimée: orge, <supplied reason="lost">la mesure, tel prix</supplied>; froment, la mesure, 2 drachmes; 
            légumineuses, <supplied reason="lost">la mesure, tel prix</supplied>; raisin sec, la mesure, <supplied reason="lost">tel prix; raisin</supplied> hâtif, <supplied reason="lost">sous</supplied> garantie, <supplied reason="lost">la mesure</supplied>, <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p><supplied reason="lost">Gods. Being damiergoi So-and-so son of So-and-so, So-and-so son of So-and-so, So-and-so</supplied> son of <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>es, being priest 
              of Apollo <supplied reason="lost" cert="low">Theuchres</supplied>tos son of Polytimos, <supplied reason="lost">the crop</supplied> was estimated: barley, <supplied reason="lost">per unit, 
              so much</supplied>; wheat, per unit, 2 drachmas; pulse, <supplied reason="lost">per unit, so much</supplied>; raisins, per unit, <supplied reason="lost">so much; grapes</supplied>, early, <supplied reason="lost">under</supplied> guarantee, <supplied reason="lost">per unit</supplied>, <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p><supplied reason="lost">Dèi. Essendo damiurghi il tale figlio del tale, il tale figlio del tale, il tale</supplied> figlio di <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>es, essendo sacerdote 
              di Apollo <supplied reason="lost" cert="low">Theuchres</supplied>tos figlio di Polytimos, <supplied reason="lost">il raccolto</supplied> è stato valutato: orzo, <supplied reason="lost">a tanto</supplied>; frumento, a 2 dracme; legumi, <supplied reason="lost">a tanto</supplied>; uva passa, <supplied reason="lost">a
                  tanto; uva</supplied>, primaticcia, garantita, <supplied reason="lost">a</supplied> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
                <p>[الآلهة. فترة كل من الداميرجوي فلان بن فلان وفلان بن فلان وفلان] بن[---] يس، كونه كاهنًا لأبوللو[ثيوخريس] توس بن بوليتيموس،[المحصول] تم تقديره كالتالي: الشعير، [للمقدار الواحد، قيمة ما]؛ القمح، للمقدار الواحد، 2 دراخما؛ البقوليات، [للمقدار الواحد ، قيمة ما]؛ الزبيب، للمقدار الواحد، [قيمة ما؛ العنب]، المبكر، [مباع] بعقد مسبق، [للمقدار الواحد]، [---].</p>
            </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>For the first edition of this corpus, the ending <foreign xml:lang="grc">-τος</foreign> had not seemed sufficient to restore the priest's name at l. 6. New arguments have been produced by <bibl><ptr target="#rosamilia2023"/></bibl> for the priest 
                Theuchrestos son of Polytimos, mentioned at <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr014800</ref> a.i.9. This is a plausible identification, which allows to be more precise about the date of this account.</p>
	<p>At line 4 the ending <foreign xml:lang="grc">-ευς</foreign> belongs to the father's name of the third damiergos, which should have a nominative in <foreign xml:lang="grc">-ης</foreign>. The length of this name cannot be determined because the line breaks do not coincide with word breaks.</p>
	<p>We follow for the second edition Rosamilia's restoration of 'figs' at line 9. However, his reading of a deteriorated nu at line 3 is neither confirmed by Paci's autopsy nor by the excellent photograph provided by the first editors; 
	    moreover, all instances of nu in this inscription (line 8) have the long hastae cut obliquely.</p>
            </div></body>
